comment: Instead of just hitting the unsubscribe button and go on with my life I thought I'd make myself useful and just give my single data point for your market research. 2 reasons (clickbaiting is the latter): 1. last few years I fell into the moderate bubble. Youtubers on this bubble went very anti-SJW and anti-PC, but over the years many went down the anti-left rabbit hole. An example would be Mr H Reviews, although a movie review channel, at one point his videos were >50% political. He recovered though, isn't trying to police the far left anymore. Your channel is just still becoming increasingly focused on this so narrowly it sounds like sensationalism. Yes you need clickbait to get views, but when the whole video really lives up to the title and thumbnail it's not clickbait anymore. This one is a good example: Johnny Depp won something, but the subject itself does not really warrant so many hours of the viewers attention over the several months and years. There's a bigger picture outside of this couple's quarrel or Brie Larson. 2. So not only you're going down this far-left social media rabbit hole, which is becoming too narrow, but you're also clickbaiting the hell out of every story. "Massive win", "Brutal loss", "Streaming failing", "Belle Delphine COMPLETELY OBLITERATES cancel culture" etc, but when you see it the stories aren't actually big profile at all, feels like wasting time on small fry.

comment:
Original Female Lead Stories: âœ“
Co-Opting Male Lead Properties and Pink Washing them: âœ–

Good movies are good movies, male or female lead.  We loved Ripley.  We loved Buffy.  Orphan Black was cool.  La Femme Nikita was solid.  The original Wonder Woman was decent.  Shows with more female-centric narratives, like Orange is the New Black and GLOW are also enjoyable, albeit with lesser appeal to a substantial proportion of hetero males.  But that's ok.  Not every film is meant for every one.  The cynicism of the Star Wars sequels was that the producers thought they could build a larger female fanbase by simply offering up an omnipotent female lead, an emo-heartthrob, some passing lip service to POC...without having to tell a compelling story or caring about the established canon of the universe.  Rather than make something of their own, Kennedy and Disney just took the franchise and mangled the story elements, going all-in on a bluff.  The core element in all of the current pink-washing, franchise maiming abominations is the same: they think too little of their audience.  They have no confidence in their ability to make quality female-centric narratives that attract an audience.  They put their politics above the necessities of myth and logos and subvert pre-established quality franchises to save themselves the risk of standing on their own two feet.   For this reason, they fail and should continue fail, at least until they stop undervaluing female-centric narratives and their audience - no more Bruce Wayne in a dress, please and thank you.  Make your own shit.
